SIMPLE: intercurrent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intercurrent
<hw>In`ter*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intercurrens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>intercurrere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>intercurrent</ets>. See <er>Intercur</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Running between or among; intervening.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au> <au>Bp. Fell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Not belonging to any
particular season.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Said of diseases occurring in
the course of another disease.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intercurrent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intercurrent
<hw>In`ter*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something
intervening.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intercutaneous</ent>⟦br⟧
